<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-04-17T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-04-17T06:00:00-05:00" n="295" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d295">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 St. Pierre-Miquelon/207:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Straus</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-17T12:00:00+01:00">April 17,
                                    1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received April 17—5:34 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>344. <hi rend="italic">Journal Officiel</hi> of April 14 carried a decree
                            containing among others the three provisions enumerated in the
                            Department’s No. 118, April 4, 6 p.m.,<note n="38" xml:id="d295fn38">Not
                                printed; for the provisions in question, subsequently embodied in
                                the decree of April 9, 1935, see note of March 15 from the French
                                Embassy, <ref target="#pg_412">p. 412</ref>.</note> in regard to
                            suppressing illicit alcohol trade from St. Pierre-Miquelon. Text of
                            decree by mail.<note n="39" xml:id="d295fn39">Despatch No. 1803, April
                                17, not printed.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Straus</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>